**Example 1: Using Resilience4j with JPA Repositories**

1. Start by creating a Spring Boot application with the following dependencies:

- spring-boot-starter-data-jpa
- spring-boot-starter-web
- resilience4j-spring-boot2 (for Spring Boot 2.x)
- resilience4j-all (optional, if you want to use all features of Resilience4j)

2. Configure your `application.properties` file with database connection settings (for H2 or any other database of your choice).

3. Define an entity and a repository for the entity:

```java
@Entity
public class Person {
    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy= GenerationType.AUTO)
    private Long id;
    private String firstName;
    private String lastName;
}

@Repository
public interface PersonRepository extends JpaRepository<Person, Long> {
    List<Person> findByLastName(String lastName);
}
```

4. Create a service class to wrap the repository call and apply Resilience4j circuit breaker functionality:

```java
import io.github.resilience4j.circuitbreaker.CircuitBreaker;
import io.github.resilience4j.circuitbreaker.CircuitBreakerConfig;

@Service
public class PersonService {

    private final PersonRepository personRepository;
    private final CircuitBreaker circuitBreaker;

    public PersonService(PersonRepository personRepository, CircuitBreakerRegistry circuitBreakerRegistry) {
        this.personRepository = personRepository;

        CircuitBreakerConfig circuitBreakerConfig = CircuitBreakerConfig.custom()
                .failureRateThreshold(50)
                .waitDurationInOpenState(Duration.ofMillis(1000))
                .ringBufferSizeInHalfOpenState(2)
                .ringBufferSizeInClosedState(2)
                .build();

        this.circuitBreaker = circuitBreakerRegistry.circuitBreaker("personService", circuitBreakerConfig);
    }

    public List<Person> findPersonsByName(String lastName) {
        return circuitBreaker.executeSupplier(() -> personRepository.findByLastName(lastName));
    }

}
```

5. In your controller, inject the `PersonService` and use it to get the persons by name:

```java
@RestController
public class PersonController {

    private final PersonService personService;

    public PersonController(PersonService personService) {
        this.personService = personService;
    }

    @GetMapping("/persons/{lastName}")
    public List<Person> getPersonsByLastName(@PathVariable String lastName) {
        return personService.findPersonsByName(lastName);
    }
}
